stream - package stream
The Stream Package porpouse is to handle all the IO operation with StreamCore and divide them for reconstruct a file with stream.input package or split a file with stream.output package and the specialized class for the type of operations (split,crypt,compress) all the operation are called by job package
stream.input - package stream.input
Input branch of stream, host the InputCore abstract class used by InputSplit, InputDecrypt and InputDecompress For process a single FileElement
stream.output - package stream.output
Output branch of stream, host the OutputCore abstract class used by OutputSplit, OutputCrypt and OutputCompress For process a single FileElement
StreamCore - Class in stream
StreamCore Abstract class, the heart of the stream package, is the generic abstract class which handle the specialized class InputCore and OutputCore This class handle the StreamCore.successfulFlag boolean operator, which update the status of all the stream operation and inform the class about the state of the file the queue is working on StreamCore host some generic utility info about the file opened, some logic calculation for the file data (a converter StreamCore.sizeConverter(logic.FileElement) for the type of information) and most important the StreamCore.writeBytes(java.io.OutputStream, long) and a StreamCore.buffer(java.io.OutputStream) used to write into a new file
StreamCore(String, FileElement) - Constructor for class stream.StreamCore
Constructor of StreamCore, get in input the output Directory and a FileElement Will start to construct the custom directory output and add the data of the file in the class variables Handle the errors in this process, advise the user abut the error via custom error message and update the FileElement status
